Sharjah Islamic Bank, Emirates NBD, RAKBank: Gulf Equity Preview

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-07-24T05:49:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-23/sharjah-islamic-bank-emirates-nbd-gulf-equity-preview.html
(Corrects Emirates NBD’s shares price)  The following stocks may rise or
fall in Persian Gulf markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and prices are from the last close.  Saudi Arabia’s  Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  advanced 0.5
percent, while Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  dropped 0.2 percent.
 Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  gained 0.2 percent.  United Development Co. (UDCD)  : The Qatari investment
company said first-half profit rose to 346.8 million riyals ($95
million) from 340.9 million riyals a year ago. The shares
dropped 0.5 percent to 20.22 riyals.  Sharjah Islamic Bank (NBS)  : The Shariah-compliant lender
based in Sharjah, the United Arab Emirates, said second-quarter
net income advanced to 53.3 million dirhams ($14.5 million) from
51 million dirhams a year earlier. The shares were unchanged at
0.88 dirhams.  Emirates NBD PJSC (EMIRATES)  : The U.A.E.’s biggest bank
by assets has been mandated along with Standard Chartered Bank
Plc, and Wells Fargo & Co. by Bank UralSib to arrange a one-year
$100 million syndicated term-loan facility. The shares were
unchanged at 4.20 dirhams.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in  Riyadh  at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net . 